1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,760
All characters and events in this series are fictional
and created solely for entertainment purposes.
Viewer discretion is advised.

2
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,000
The villain everyone’s been wondering about…

3
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:45,520
It’s me.

4
00:01:47,320 --> 00:01:49,080
Long time no see, P’Peach.

5
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,000
If you’re talking about “Cute”

6
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,039
Cute is not my ex.

7
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,000
What do you want, Ya?

8
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:58,479
If I tell you… will you give me what I want?

9
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:01,880
We’ve been running into each other quite often lately. Do you know why?

10
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:03,520
I’ve already solved the problem for you.

11
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:11,520
I will never let Sun get hurt.

12
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:13,800
What are you guys watching?

13
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,840
Is that Maya’s latest post?

14
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:17,880
Why didn’t you tell me you were done with work?

15
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,520
P’Flint, you don’t have to pick me up.

16
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:21,680
P’Jan asked Sun to stay over as company.

17
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,720
I hope you don’t have a problem with that.

18
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:27,480
Even my little sister doesn’t have a problem with what you did.

19
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:41,680
(Online headline: “Clip resembling famous actress goes viral — extremely explicit”)

20
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,720
Khun Mo! Khun Mo!

21
00:02:48,880 --> 00:02:53,480
Right now, every platform of our channel
is flooded with comments pressuring us about the news.

22
00:03:05,720 --> 00:03:07,120
Have you been able to reach Sun?

23
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:09,440
The team has been calling her since this morning,

24
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,840
but she’s not answering.

25
00:03:13,640 --> 00:03:15,840
Then call Mooham to see me immediately.

26
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,920
If you still can’t reach her, go to her condo.

27
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,440
Yes, ma’am.

28
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,400
Why aren’t you answering your phone, Sun?

29
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:40,560
Fey, you’re going to see Sun, right?

30
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:50,360
Yes, I’m on my way now. Okay.

31
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,920
Let’s go, Sun.

32
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,440
Are you okay?

33
00:03:53,440 --> 00:03:54,200
Sun is here!

34
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,280
Oh! Sun!

35
00:03:55,640 --> 00:03:59,880
- Sun, can you tell us what’s going on with the clip?
- The woman in the video looks a lot like you.

36
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:03,840
And who’s the man in the clip? Aren’t you dating Khun Rafah?

37
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,840
- That’s right.
- Yeah, isn’t that true?

38
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:08,680
Please calm down, everyone. Please calm down.

39
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:11,320
The person in the clip is not Sun.

40
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,560
- Oh?
- It’s not?

41
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:14,240
Please make some room for Sun.

42
00:04:14,240 --> 00:04:15,760
Excuse us. I’m sorry.

43
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:17,959
Sun, please answer us!

44
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:21,399
Please calm down. Make some space for her.

45
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:23,080
Please answer!

46
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:24,920
Sun!

47
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,760
Why are there so many reporters in front of the station?

48
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:53,960
P’Mooham, that’s not even a question. The news is huge.

49
00:04:54,159 --> 00:04:56,520
The staff hasn’t had a break since this morning.

50
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,080
We still don’t know who uploaded it.

51
00:04:59,080 --> 00:05:00,360
How did you get here?

52
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:03,240
Why didn’t you go back to your room last night, Sun?

53
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:05,800
Do you know I waited for you all night?

54
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:13,760
Sun, the executives are asking for you in the meeting room. Urgently.

55
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,440
Excuse me.

56
00:05:17,760 --> 00:05:19,760
I’m going with her.

57
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,640
How strange.

58
00:05:24,920 --> 00:05:26,400
Running into you here.

59
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:33,760
Living up to your nickname, the angel of the entertainment industry.

60
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:37,360
Whatever you do always draws attention,

61
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:43,120
whether it’s something good… or something bad.

62
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:44,920
Ya.

63
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,360
If Khun Rafah is coming, you’d better hurry.

64
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:53,000
I don’t want the executives waiting too long for Sun.

65
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:54,720
Excuse me, Khun Maya.

66
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,640
But it seems like…

67
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:03,840
your “good person” might make history repeat itself, Flint.

68
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:21,520
This is the preliminary damage report from the leaked clip.

69
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,480
I told you before, didn’t I? Don’t let any more problems happen.

70
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:27,440
Why didn’t you listen?

71
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:31,320
Sun stayed at my room all night.

72
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:34,360
I can be her witness.

73
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:38,120
Either way, the person in the clip is definitely not Sun.

74
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,680
A witness?

75
00:06:39,880 --> 00:06:42,320
A witness who’s her own manager?

76
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:46,080
Mooham…

77
00:06:46,600 --> 00:06:48,720
Stop acting like a rookie.

78
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:50,360
You’ve been in this industry long enough.

79
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:55,400
The solution isn’t a witness. It’s evidence.

80
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:58,840
So how is the channel supposed to respond?

81
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:01,160
But according to basic principles,

82
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:04,240
before punishing someone,

83
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:09,080
shouldn’t there be a clear investigation first to confirm
whether they’re actually guilty?

84
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:12,680
I think the channel handling it this way

85
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,440
is shifting the problem onto the artist

86
00:07:15,440 --> 00:07:19,000
instead of protecting her which is what you’re supposed to do.

87
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:28,240
Khun Rafah,

88
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:32,120
have you even seen the clip yet?

89
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:45,960
Please watch the clip in here for me.

90
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:49,159
I had my staff enhance the brightness of the clip.

91
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:53,560
Khun Rafah, after you watch it, please confirm for me

92
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:58,720
whether the woman in the video is the person you’re currently seeing.

93
00:08:00,560 --> 00:08:05,040
Because from what I’ve seen ever since Sun first stepped into this channel

94
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:09,920
I still can’t find any excuse

95
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:12,920
to say that the woman in the clip isn’t Sun Atita.

96
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:40,960
I’ll take responsibility for everything that happened.

97
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:06,600
Why should you take responsibility for something you didn’t even do?

98
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:09,720
The more you say that, the more people will misunderstand

99
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,680
and think you're really the woman in the clip.

100
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:18,960
If even the person closest to me isn’t confident in me…

101
00:09:19,440 --> 00:09:21,440
then I don’t expect anyone else to believe me either.

102
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,000
Sun, can you listen to me first?

103
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:35,520
P’Sun… you’re not the woman in the clip, right?

104
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:38,320
We don’t believe you would do something like that.

105
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:40,160
How did you all get in here?

106
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:42,240
This area is for staff only.

107
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:45,200
P’Sun, can you answer us first? Are you the woman in the clip or not?

108
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:48,680
I think you should all go home first.

109
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:53,560
As for the news, we’ll arrange for Sun to hold a press conference as soon as possible.

110
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:56,320
If you didn’t do it, then why won’t you just say so?

111
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:58,680
We can see your face clearly in the clip. Disgusting.

112
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:01,440
Yeah. Such a waste supporting you. Didn’t think you’d be this promiscuous.

113
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:02,280
- Yes.
- Right.

114
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:04,000
There she is! Sun’s over there! Hurry!

115
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,440
- Sun! What’s going on between you and Khun Rafah?
- Are you two still together?

116
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:10,640
There’s nothing going on. There’s really nothing.

117
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:17,000
Stop pretending already!

118
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:20,520
Hey! They threw water at her!

119
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:22,120
Sun, are you okay?

120
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,360
Wait…

121
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,480
Why...

122
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:42,320
does P’Nop’s tattoo look exactly like the man’s in the clip?

123
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:44,280
- Oh my god.
- Right?

124
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:48,800
Does that mean Nop is the man in the clip with Sun?

125
00:10:49,320 --> 00:10:50,920
- Is it the same person?
- Is it?

126
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:54,240
- What do you have to say?
- This is definitely not true.

127
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:55,760
Are you two the people in the clip?

128
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:07,600
- Sun, come with me.
- Move, move!

129
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:11,720
Sun!

130
00:11:14,680 --> 00:11:18,920
- Where are you taking her?
- Sun! Sun!

131
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:35,120
Fey, calm down first.

132
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:39,080
I believe Khun Rafah is probably trying to find a solution right now too.

133
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:45,040
But what Sun needs most right now is encouragement and trust
from the person who’s supposed to be her girlfriend.

134
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:49,040
I believe Sun isn’t afraid of the clip going viral.

135
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:51,360
Because it’s not true anyway.

136
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:56,240
What she’s really afraid of is being devalued by the person she loves the most.

137
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:05,840
Let’s talk in the room.

138
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:10,160
Why didn’t you go to Sun, P’Flint?

139
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,360
Why are you still at the office?

140
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:17,120
When right now, Sun needs you more than anyone.

141
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:19,720
Why are you doing this?

142
00:12:25,520 --> 00:12:28,920
Do I really have to spell it out for you why I’m here?

143
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:32,200
As Deputy Managing Director,

144
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,600
you should understand better than anyone…

145
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:38,320
what kind of impact this situation has on Sun.

146
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:41,880
On Sun?

147
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:43,840
Or on the company?

148
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:45,520
Fey.

149
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:53,040
I know this company means everything to you, P’Flint.

150
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:58,880
But I hope… my best friend means just as much.

151
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:10,480
(“I’m picking up the car tomorrow. Hope we get to see each other, Flint.”)

152
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,720
Hey, she’s here!

153
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,080
Excuse me, may we have an interview?

154
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:34,080
Sorry, please make way!

155
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:36,720
Khun Rafah, can we get a comment?

156
00:15:36,720 --> 00:15:38,320
Hello, Khun Rafah.

157
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:40,480
Why are there so many reporters crowding the front of your showroom?

158
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:43,360
Khun Rafah, regarding your relationship with Khun Sun Atita

159
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:45,160
you just announced you were dating.

160
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:48,320
Now that this clip has surfaced, has it shaken your relationship?

161
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:51,680
Yes, Khun Rafah, please answer.

162
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:54,040
If you don’t respond, it will only reinforce the rumors

163
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:56,760
that a high-society heiress has been cheated on by her rising-star girlfriend.

164
00:15:56,760 --> 00:15:58,800
Yes, Khun Rafah, please answer.

165
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:03,640
You’re crossing the line.

166
00:16:04,880 --> 00:16:09,600
- Crossing the line? We’re just doing our job.
- That’s right.

167
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,600
Why are you so late, Flint?

168
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:22,560
The more you talk, the longer this drags on. You know that.

169
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:27,440
Everyone, we’ll excuse ourselves first.

170
00:16:27,440 --> 00:16:31,880
As for the news, it’s better to wait for Sun to make her own statement.

171
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:34,000
Let’s go, Flint.

172
00:16:34,680 --> 00:16:38,320
I have prepared the vehicle documents in the lounge for Khun Maya.

173
00:16:38,720 --> 00:16:40,960
Have them sent to my office instead.

174
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,160
Yes, Madam.

175
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:02,320
You can wait here for a bit.

176
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:04,920
The documents should arrive shortly.

177
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:07,440
I’m not in a rush.

178
00:17:35,080 --> 00:17:36,080
Are you stressed?

179
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:50,760
Then maybe we should…

180
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:58,000
find something

181
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:00,800
to help you relax?

182
00:18:25,840 --> 00:18:27,080
I just found out

183
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:31,120
that your office isn’t only for work, P’Flint.

184
00:18:34,840 --> 00:18:37,040
P’Ya is just waiting for the car documents.

185
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,920
Did you need something, Fey?

186
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:44,240
I was going to ask you to go see Sun.

187
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:46,560
But now I understand…

188
00:18:46,560 --> 00:18:50,280
you’re probably too busy to visit your own girlfriend.

189
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,040
Make yourself comfortable.

190
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:15,800
Right now, I have people tracking down who leaked Sun’s clip.

191
00:19:17,080 --> 00:19:19,640
I think it’s better for Sun to stay with Jan for now.

192
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:24,000
If there’s any update, I’ll inform you immediately.

193
00:19:24,240 --> 00:19:26,240
How are you holding up, P’Mooham?

194
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:32,840
I’m fine. You should worry about yourself, Sun.

195
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:35,160
We don’t know what else is coming.

196
00:19:35,840 --> 00:19:38,600
I’ll call you again later.

197
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:48,520
P’Mooham…

198
00:19:49,200 --> 00:19:52,360
The department head asked me to collect your staff ID card.

199
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,040
Sun.

200
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:36,800
If you’ve got company,

201
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,640
I’ll go pick up Jan first.

202
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,120
She should be done at the embassy by now.

203
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:43,560
I’ll get going.

204
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,800
And you…

205
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:54,200
how did you get here?

206
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:58,280
Have you eaten?

207
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,640
Mm.

208
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:19,520
How are you, Sun?

209
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,280
I’m okay.

210
00:21:29,080 --> 00:21:33,280
Staying here… P’Jan and P’Win are taking good care of me.

211
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:36,000
You don’t have to worry.

212
00:21:40,640 --> 00:21:45,760
I’m not worried that Khun Jan and Khun Phuwin won’t take care of you.

213
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:50,480
What I’m worried about… is how you’re feeling.

214
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:57,120
Stop pretending to be strong

215
00:21:58,840 --> 00:22:00,680
when you’re clearly not okay, Sun.

216
00:22:15,640 --> 00:22:18,320
I don’t know what I’m supposed to do anymore, Fey.

217
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:23,000
Everyone thinks I’m guilty…

218
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:26,760
even though I haven’t done anything.

219
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,520
I’m tired.

220
00:22:33,440 --> 00:22:35,280
I’m so tired, Fey.

221
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:50,720
Even if the whole world doesn’t believe you… that’s okay.

222
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:55,800
I will.

223
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,440
And I’ll always stand by you, Sun.

224
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:16,520
Don’t cry.

225
00:24:26,160 --> 00:24:27,880
P’Ya.

226
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:30,760
Oh, Sun.

227
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:33,640
You came without telling anyone?

228
00:24:51,520 --> 00:24:54,760
Looks like Flint has a guest.

229
00:25:02,160 --> 00:25:05,600
In that case, I can leave first…

230
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,800
in case you two need to talk.

231
00:25:08,360 --> 00:25:09,680
It’s okay.

232
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,160
I should get going anyway.

233
00:25:17,200 --> 00:25:19,160
Sorry for disturbing you.

234
00:27:18,960 --> 00:27:20,960
If you want to follow her,

235
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:24,160
I can cancel our dinner tonight.

236
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:35,880
You know…

237
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:39,000
I don’t like being made a fool.

238
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:01,000
And what exactly do you like?

239
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:11,760
I was just teasing.

240
00:28:28,400 --> 00:28:32,000
You know what I like.

241
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:02,640
Like this?

242
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:05,560
Is this what you like, Flint?

243
00:29:14,280 --> 00:29:15,760
I like it too.

244
00:29:23,800 --> 00:29:25,800
In this clip… who would you rather be with?

245
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:28,200
What is this, Flint?

246
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:39,200
You know I love catching liars.

247
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:43,520
I forgot to introduce myself.

248
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:45,160
My name is Peach.

249
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:47,680
I run a visual effects company.

250
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:52,800
So it’s not strange that I can tell Sun’s leaked clip was digitally altered.

251
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:56,120
You probably didn’t know…

252
00:29:56,120 --> 00:29:59,120
AI doesn’t render reflections in mirrors properly, Ya.

253
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:10,960
And one more thing you should know...

254
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:13,800
I remember every inch of Sun’s body.

255
00:30:13,800 --> 00:30:16,560
- That’s enough, Flint.
- Ya, stop.

256
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:23,560
I wanted this to end in this room

257
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:27,000
because I was hoping you’d stop.

258
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:30,120
Stop all this madness.

259
00:30:32,720 --> 00:30:37,560
Consider this my apology for using you as Sun’s replacement.

260
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:41,520
You’re disgusting, Flint.

261
00:30:44,360 --> 00:30:47,120
I hope you take this final chance, Ya.

262
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,800
Sun…

263
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:53,560
About last night, I’m sorry.

264
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:56,040
Can you let me explain?

265
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:06,000
I told you before, didn’t I?

266
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:09,920
If you ever make my sister cry, I won’t let you off.

267
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:12,080
Khun Jan.

268
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:13,840
Where is Sun?

269
00:33:13,840 --> 00:33:16,000
You still dare to ask about my sister?

270
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:19,040
Have you ever once thought about what you’ve done to her?

271
00:33:20,840 --> 00:33:22,800
I know you’re angry.

272
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:26,000
Everything that happened I can explain.

273
00:33:26,960 --> 00:33:30,560
But can you please tell me first where Sun is?

274
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:39,600
Khun Rafah,

275
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:42,280
Do you know that Sun is holding a press conference today?

276
00:33:42,760 --> 00:33:43,760
A press conference?

277
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:48,480
Yes. In two hours. She’ll be addressing the leaked photos and the clip.

278
00:33:54,680 --> 00:33:56,400
After today,

279
00:33:57,120 --> 00:33:59,360
I’m taking my sister to America with me.

280
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,480
Khun Jan...

281
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:36,639
They’re here. Sun and Nop have arrived.

282
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:52,120
Hello to all the reporters here today.

283
00:34:54,080 --> 00:35:00,320
First of all, I would like to apologize to my agency
for the negative impact caused by this controversy.

284
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:06,840
And to my fans, who have always given me love and support.

285
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:11,040
I’m fully aware

286
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:15,360
that what happened is something many people may find unforgivable.

287
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:19,280
But I would like to use this space

288
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:26,720
to sincerely apologize to everyone
and to society for the damage that has occurred.

289
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:30,640
So by saying that, are you admitting that

290
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:34,440
the leaked photos and clip are really you?

291
00:35:34,720 --> 00:35:37,480
Is that correct?

292
00:35:37,480 --> 00:35:39,200
Sun, please answer.

293
00:35:39,200 --> 00:35:44,120
- Is it really you?
- Please tell us if it’s true.

294
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:50,280
Sun doesn't the person in the clip.

295
00:35:50,280 --> 00:35:52,040
Huh?

296
00:36:04,240 --> 00:36:07,040
That video was edited

297
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:10,280
to create negative publicity against Sun.

298
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:20,160
The documents you’ve all received

299
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:22,640
are official reports from institutions where I submitted the clip

300
00:36:22,640 --> 00:36:27,280
for forensic analysis both in Thailand and overseas.

301
00:36:27,280 --> 00:36:29,840
As you can see, the enhanced images are much clearer.

302
00:36:29,840 --> 00:36:31,840
The metadata analysis

303
00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:35,520
and pixel-level software examination

304
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:38,960
revealed overlapping frame manipulation on the subject’s face.

305
00:36:39,280 --> 00:36:44,160
In conclusion, the clip was digitally altered and fabricated.

306
00:36:55,480 --> 00:36:58,720
However… if you want to know who the real person in the clip is

307
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,640
you should ask Mr. Nop.

308
00:37:06,920 --> 00:37:07,960
Everyone…

309
00:37:08,280 --> 00:37:11,160
The reason I’m here today is to tell you clearly

310
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:13,440
the woman in the leaked clip is not Sun.

311
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:22,520
But regarding the previously leaked photos…

312
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:27,680
I would like to take this opportunity to accept responsibility for all of them.

313
00:37:28,240 --> 00:37:30,080
Responsibility for what?

314
00:37:36,800 --> 00:37:40,280
Those photos are of me and Phuwin.

315
00:37:52,640 --> 00:37:55,240
I am Sun’s twin sister.

316
00:38:09,360 --> 00:38:12,760
No more excuses, Mr. Annop.

317
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:51,920
Sun, can you listen to me?

318
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:07,080
Everything I did

319
00:39:08,280 --> 00:39:09,840
I did it for you.

320
00:39:21,560 --> 00:39:23,200
Thank you.

321
00:39:25,680 --> 00:39:27,520
But for me…

322
00:39:28,560 --> 00:39:30,480
what I needed most

323
00:39:31,720 --> 00:39:37,440
was simply to have the people I love standing beside me
during the worst time of my life.

324
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,680
And yet, you chose to leave me alone.

325
00:39:49,520 --> 00:39:51,240
Excuse me.

326
00:40:08,200 --> 00:40:10,040
- Viewer, P’Oui!
- Yes?

327
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:12,800
There’s something like… oh my God, seriously shocking!

328
00:40:12,800 --> 00:40:16,440
After Sun Atita held a major press conference

329
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,840
and clearly presented solid evidence

330
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:24,840
confirming that she was not the person in the leaked clip

331
00:40:24,840 --> 00:40:27,160
the drama ended overnight!

332
00:40:27,520 --> 00:40:29,400
But shortly after that, P’Oui…

333
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:32,480
- The entertainment industry was shaken once again.
- Oh, goosebumps!

334
00:40:32,480 --> 00:40:33,760
- And you know why?
- Why?

335
00:40:33,760 --> 00:40:38,240
Because Nop and Maya have officially withdrawn from this big-budget series.

336
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:41,880
And as if social media wasn’t already on fire, it exploded even more!

337
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:46,080
And most importantly, everyone is asking

338
00:40:46,080 --> 00:40:49,240
Was this really just a change of plans?

339
00:40:49,240 --> 00:40:52,000
Or is there something suspicious

340
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:53,840
going on behind the scenes?

341
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:55,800
- What do you think, P’Oui? /
- Behind the scenes, obviously.

342
00:40:59,720 --> 00:41:02,280
The media these days is terrifying.

343
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:07,800
One mistake, and they dig until you can’t rise again.

344
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:10,600
You’re saying that like you’re not media yourself.

345
00:41:11,760 --> 00:41:14,160
Well, I’m not anymore.

346
00:41:14,800 --> 00:41:20,480
I’m now an independent artist manager reporting directly to Sun Atita only.

347
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:24,080
Honestly…

348
00:41:24,240 --> 00:41:28,360
I still can’t believe the woman in the clip was really Maya.

349
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:30,920
When I heard it from Khun Rafah and Peach,

350
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:33,200
I was really shocked

351
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:36,920
when I realized it was Maya.

352
00:41:42,160 --> 00:41:45,800
Sun… you still haven’t talked to Khun Rafah?

353
00:41:46,240 --> 00:41:48,040
It’s been several days already.

354
00:41:50,200 --> 00:41:54,680
I think P’Ya had her reasons for what she did.

355
00:41:55,520 --> 00:41:59,400
No one wants to be the villain in someone else’s eyes.

356
00:42:01,160 --> 00:42:06,160
Sun… I know you’re someone who always sees the good in people.

357
00:42:06,840 --> 00:42:09,840
Then can you try to see the good intentions

358
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:12,320
behind what Khun Rafah did for you?

359
00:42:13,760 --> 00:42:18,720
I know she made a mistake by leaving you alone.

360
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:21,000
But everything she did

361
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:25,040
was to clear your name from something you didn’t even do.

362
00:43:14,120 --> 00:43:16,200
Come. I'll help you.

363
00:43:25,520 --> 00:43:28,560
When I’ve been filming a lot and my eyes feel tired,

364
00:43:29,120 --> 00:43:30,560
I do this.

365
00:43:31,320 --> 00:43:32,600
P’Flint, close your eyes.

366
00:43:47,440 --> 00:43:48,760
How do you feel?

367
00:44:06,560 --> 00:44:08,440
- Sun, are you okay?
- I’m okay.

368
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:10,920
Hi, Sun. Hi, P’Mooham. How have you been?

369
00:44:11,080 --> 00:44:13,080
Hello! It’s been a while.

370
00:44:13,440 --> 00:44:14,560
I’m good.

371
00:44:14,880 --> 00:44:17,080
We took a two-month break from the series.

372
00:44:17,280 --> 00:44:20,120
First day back on set I’m so excited!

373
00:44:20,120 --> 00:44:22,800
Looks like you are even more excited than Sun.

374
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:26,480
Oh, and your delivery is already in the dressing room.

375
00:44:26,480 --> 00:44:28,320
Flowers?

376
00:44:28,320 --> 00:44:29,840
No. It's food support.

377
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:34,360
Then which way is the dressing room? I’ll take her there myself.

378
00:44:34,360 --> 00:44:35,120
This way.

379
00:44:44,560 --> 00:44:46,880
Sun… I’m sorry.

380
00:44:47,280 --> 00:44:49,960
I went to pick you up this morning,

381
00:44:49,960 --> 00:44:51,680
but I didn’t see any flowers from Khun Rafah.

382
00:44:52,080 --> 00:44:54,080
I thought maybe she’d send them to the set.

383
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:58,640
It’s strange though, she usually sends them every day.

384
00:45:00,520 --> 00:45:02,440
Maybe she’s tired of sending them.

385
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:05,960
Let’s go, P’Mooham.

386
00:45:16,840 --> 00:45:21,200
Let’s keep the makeup tone soft, please. Fresh, like a student.

387
00:45:22,080 --> 00:45:23,360
All done, Khun Mooham.

388
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:25,880
Okay, thank you.

389
00:45:28,040 --> 00:45:29,280
Let me see…

390
00:45:29,800 --> 00:45:34,320
Wow, Sun really does look forever young.

391
00:45:34,760 --> 00:45:38,600
I didn’t even know this role required a school uniform.

392
00:45:39,240 --> 00:45:41,800
And the location is my old school too.

393
00:45:41,800 --> 00:45:45,160
It’s a flashback scene. The director added it.

394
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:47,920
They even asked me to write on Sun’s shirt before the scene.

395
00:45:48,760 --> 00:45:51,200
Come on, let me pick a spot first.

396
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:52,760
Here should be good.

397
00:46:01,640 --> 00:46:02,880
Can I write something too?

398
00:46:02,880 --> 00:46:04,040
How did you get here?

399
00:46:04,560 --> 00:46:07,000
Thank you. Turn around, turn around.

400
00:46:07,760 --> 00:46:08,840
What should I write?

401
00:46:15,920 --> 00:46:18,000
It feels like we’ve gone back to graduation day, doesn’t it?

402
00:46:19,520 --> 00:46:21,160
Then why are you writing on the back?

403
00:46:23,360 --> 00:46:24,440
There’s more space.

404
00:46:26,880 --> 00:46:28,600
P’Peach, do you want to write something too?

405
00:46:32,680 --> 00:46:34,400
Khun Peach, would you like to?

406
00:46:35,240 --> 00:46:37,480
You can call me P’Peach. It sounds cuter.

407
00:46:40,600 --> 00:46:41,960
Come here, I’ll write it.

408
00:46:51,120 --> 00:46:53,000
Cute. Right here on the heart.

409
00:46:56,360 --> 00:46:59,640
Sun, 10 minutes. Please be ready for set.

410
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:00,920
Okay.

411
00:47:06,720 --> 00:47:09,080
I think we should add more.

412
00:47:09,320 --> 00:47:11,160
I want to write something too!

413
00:47:11,160 --> 00:47:11,960
What about you, Sun?

414
00:47:15,560 --> 00:47:17,640
Do you remember? This is the field we used to come to all the time.

415
00:47:17,640 --> 00:47:19,600
And we’d sit over there. We like the same food too.

416
00:47:19,600 --> 00:47:21,720
- Yeah, I remember. We’d just sit here all day.
- Yeah.

417
00:47:21,720 --> 00:47:23,520
And honestly, the atmosphere is really nice.

418
00:47:24,000 --> 00:47:26,680
Hey, let me take this call first. I’ll catch up with you.

419
00:47:26,680 --> 00:47:27,360
Okay.

420
00:47:27,840 --> 00:47:29,160
P’Peach, could you come with me for a second?

421
00:47:29,400 --> 00:47:30,160
Sure.

422
00:47:32,400 --> 00:47:35,400
- They’re actually really cute together, aren’t they?
- Yes, P’Mooham.

423
00:47:36,360 --> 00:47:37,560
Watch out!

424
00:47:50,920 --> 00:47:52,040
Sorry! I’m so sorry!

425
00:48:05,720 --> 00:48:06,920
That was close, wasn’t it?

426
00:48:10,440 --> 00:48:11,520
That was really close.

427
00:48:12,080 --> 00:48:13,080
Thank you.

428
00:48:14,560 --> 00:48:15,440
You’re okay, right?

429
00:48:16,000 --> 00:48:17,480
Are you okay?

430
00:48:18,520 --> 00:48:19,360
Let’s go.

431
00:48:27,800 --> 00:48:30,120
Sun, let’s go.

432
00:48:33,680 --> 00:48:38,320
Ugh, I seriously don’t get it. What does “diffusion” even mean?

433
00:48:39,720 --> 00:48:41,120
Did I not explain it clearly?

434
00:48:51,640 --> 00:48:55,080
It’s kind of like falling in love with someone.

435
00:48:57,320 --> 00:48:58,160
Right?

436
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:06,600
Sun, your makeup is ready.

437
00:49:07,440 --> 00:49:08,120
Okay.

438
00:49:20,040 --> 00:49:21,280
P’Flint…

439
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:43,920
Can you write something on my shirt?

440
00:50:12,640 --> 00:50:14,360
You once told me that…

441
00:50:15,680 --> 00:50:16,800
I never knew

442
00:50:18,200 --> 00:50:19,600
how Sun felt about me.

443
00:50:27,680 --> 00:50:30,000
(I like you, Sun.)

444
00:50:31,440 --> 00:50:35,400
But the truth is, you never really knew either

445
00:50:37,160 --> 00:50:38,720
how I felt about you.

446
00:50:41,440 --> 00:50:43,120
Lik...

447
00:50:53,160 --> 00:50:54,880
Good luck.

448
00:50:55,800 --> 00:50:57,200
I’m sorry…

449
00:50:58,800 --> 00:51:03,640
that day… I wasn’t brave enough to tell you how I felt.

450
00:51:06,200 --> 00:51:07,680
But today,

451
00:51:09,320 --> 00:51:11,720
I won’t let you walk out of my life again.

452
00:51:20,400 --> 00:51:21,480
I love you, Sun.

453
00:51:28,880 --> 00:51:30,880
Will you give me a chance

454
00:51:31,440 --> 00:51:33,120
to stay by your side like this, forever?

455
00:51:41,520 --> 00:51:42,640
Our friend finally got her happy ending.

456
00:51:42,960 --> 00:51:45,600
So… will you agree to go on a date with me now?

457
00:51:49,440 --> 00:51:52,120
I bought these flowers for you.

458
00:51:55,080 --> 00:51:55,880
Thank you.

459
00:51:55,880 --> 00:52:00,440
Wow, that’s so sweet.
Not even trying to hide it. Sweeter than that couple over there, maybe.

460
00:52:00,440 --> 00:52:02,360
P’Mooham, don’t you want to find someone too?

461
00:52:03,040 --> 00:52:06,560
Prang, Warang, being sweet again, huh?

462
00:52:07,000 --> 00:52:09,520
Nine years of waiting… congratulations, Sun.

463
00:52:18,920 --> 00:52:20,240
I love you too, P’Flint.

464
00:52:20,880 --> 00:52:23,320
Kiss! Kiss! Kiss!

465
00:52:47,000 --> 00:52:48,200
I love you, P’Flint.

466
00:52:53,000 --> 00:52:54,120
And I love you too, Sun.

467
00:53:28,040 --> 00:53:29,320
Once…

468
00:53:29,480 --> 00:53:32,240
I let my sun set beyond the horizon,

469
00:53:33,040 --> 00:53:36,800
without ever realizing how long that night would be.

470
00:53:47,680 --> 00:53:49,880
It became the quietest

471
00:53:50,360 --> 00:53:53,280
and darkest period in the life of a sky like me.

472
00:54:00,000 --> 00:54:01,080
But this time…

473
00:54:03,440 --> 00:54:06,160
if I’m given the chance

474
00:54:09,640 --> 00:54:12,600
to meet my sun again, I won’t let it disappear.

475
00:54:13,320 --> 00:54:16,760
And I’ll hold onto it for as long as I possibly can.

476
00:54:20,760 --> 00:54:22,080
Not because I’m afraid of the dark,

477
00:54:23,160 --> 00:54:24,240
but because I know

478
00:54:25,160 --> 00:54:29,760
that a sky like me could never be bright or beautiful

479
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:36,440
without the light from a sun like you.

480
00:56:00,120 --> 00:56:01,520
Hello, dear diary.

481
00:56:01,960 --> 00:56:04,360
Today, I opened this notebook again.

482
00:56:05,280 --> 00:56:06,440
It’s kind of funny, isn’t it?

483
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:08,440
The Sun from back then

484
00:56:09,120 --> 00:56:11,720
would’ve never imagined that today I’d be writing these words:

485
00:56:12,480 --> 00:56:14,560
I’m P’Flint’s girlfriend now.

486
00:56:14,960 --> 00:56:17,120
Not just her best friend’s little sister.

487
00:56:18,000 --> 00:56:20,520
Not just someone chasing after someone else’s shadow.

488
00:56:21,680 --> 00:56:25,680
I’m finally myself at the right time.

489
00:56:26,480 --> 00:56:27,840
Thank you to myself

490
00:56:28,920 --> 00:56:30,640
for giving everything a chance.

491
00:56:31,360 --> 00:56:33,760
Some things went wrong, some things went right,

492
00:56:34,720 --> 00:56:36,840
but I love where I am now the most.
